props.synopsis: Australia's official terror alert level has been raised to "probable" amid heightened community tensions over the war in Gaza.

title.children: ASIO lifts terror threat level to 'probable' amid heightened tensions over war in Gaza

image.altText: Young woman surrounded by pets

props.synopsis: Tasmanian independent MP David O'Byrne is pushing for a change to state laws to make harming or threatening a pet, with the intent to coerce, intimidate or control a spouse or partner, a form of family violence.

title.children: 'It should be defined as family violence': MP calls for Tasmanian law change to recognise harm to pets

image.altText: A stock trader looks down at a tablet as he works on the floor of a busy stock exchange while surrounded by screens.

props.synopsis: The ASX plummets 3 per cent, extending the falls it made on Friday in what is the index's worst two-day performance since 2022. Follow the day's events and insights from our business reporters on the ABC News live markets blog.

title.children: ASX plummets 3pc in worst two-day performance since 2022

image.altText: a man in a hard hat looks on at a large piece of machinery

image.altText: A nurse wearing hair net and mask, seen from behind, with other nurses in a group.

image.altText: Close-up image of a McDonald's Big Mac burger on light coloured background

image.altText: Two Australian teammates stand smiling arm in arm with Australian flags after the women's high jump final.

image.altText: Noah Lyles roars with delight while holding up an American flag

image.altText: A shot of a busy Melbourne street with pedestrians in front of a tram.

image.altText: A portrait of an older man wearing a black beanie and maroon, yellow and green in a room.

image.altText: A mean wearing a shirt and tie with his jacket over his shoulder stands on a race track.

image.altText: Two men sit at a press conference table with blue microphones in front of them

image.altText: Indigenous women at night time looking at the camera.
